                                "id": "01GR6AFCC93PF6T4EYVTXXYJY9",
                                "reference": "INSPIRATION",
                                "subject": "Inspiration"
                            },
                            "text": "Rooted in Japanese folklore, tengu are mythical creatures with many faces. They were originally tormentors and malicious, but their image evolved over the years, and they eventually became pious and protective. Yet becoming a tengu always results from a mistake that must be atoned for: having chosen the path of anger, ambition, vanity and pride."
                        },
